title: GM_Eni-0
body:
<<changeNPCAnimation Gm_Eni 0>> SKIP
SKIP
Hello and welcome to Caballa Island!\n(Clapping~) I am GM Eni.
<<changeNPCAnimation Gm_Eni 1>> You have to listen to me carefully and answer some questions, and if you answer them correctly I will\npresent you with Rookie Sword and Rookie Shield as a gift.
<<startQuest 1>>SKIP
<<changeNPCAnimation Gm_Eni 0>>Well first, I want to explain the basic interface you see on the game screen...
What you see on the left side is a graph which indicates your current information on...
Level and Experience, Stamina(HP), Mana(MP), Galders(Currency), and Weight, this can be useful in helping you with control of the game.
In Trickster, you can register up to 3 layers of 8 actions each for a total of 24 into Quick Slot system.
This is ideal for quickly accessing often used items, skills and weapons that registered to the slots.
You can use the actions registered via the keys on your keyboard from F1 to F8 and it makes for much easier use of key game elements.
Quick slots 1 can be hidden or shown by using the "T" key on a keyboard. Make sure not to forget these things I told you.
In the bottom left corner of the screen is the chatting window.
Here you can receive memos, whisper to others, and of course chat.
The icons you see on the right side of the bottom of the window indicate categories which are necessary for game play.
If you move the mouse over each menu item, a small window will pop up which you can click on to open the interface.
A letter given in a red color indicates the Shortcut Key that can be used to open the item quickly.
Basically that's all there is to know about the\ninterface you see in the game screen, Did it help\n you?\nOK then, here's a Quiz and if you get it right, I'll give you a present.
[[GM_ENI_TryAgainQuestion]]

title: Pia-0
body:
<<changeNPCAnimation Pia 1>> SKIP
SKIP
Hello, my name is Pia. I'm one of the members of the 7-Princess Club.
I will explain to you the ways to use shops in the game.
If you can listen to my tutorial carefully, I will give you a Rookie Hat.
Inventory Window is where you keep track of money, cards and other items that you may pick up as you proceed in the game.
First, you can check your items as well as galders you collected in Item Inventory, but then there's Card Inventory as well, for managing your cards.
To open up the item Inventory Window, click on the Item button at the menu or press the shortcut key "I".
In order to open up the  Card Inventory, click on the card button or the shortcut key "C".
In order to use an item, double click on the item you wan or simply press the Use button.
Equipment, Drill, Pet are easily equipped by double clicking on them.
If you want to know the information about an item, press view button, or click on the right button of the mouse, then you will see some useful information about the item.
How do you drop an Item?
It's easy, Just press the Drop Button or drag an item out of the Item Window.
Should I proceed to explain how to use the store?
<<changeNPCAnimation Pia 1>>Do you see Item Girl? She is also a member of the 7-Princess Club. Hoho~
<<changeNPCAnimation Pia 0>>You can sell your items or buy an item from her at the Item Shop.
To make a purchase, select the number of items you want to buy using the arrow button, and click on the BUY button to finalize the purchase.
<<changeNPCAnimation Pia 0>>
<<giveGalder 1000>> 
<<startQuest 4>>
<<changeNPCState Item_Girl Item_Girl-0>>
<<changeNPCState Pia Pia-1>>
Well can you go to the Item Girl and buy me Tangerine?
Go talk to Item Girl over there. I'll be waiting.

title: Magician_Sephira-0
body:
<<changeNPCAnimation Magician_Sephira 1>>SKIP
SKIP
Hello, I am Magician Sephira.\nI will tell you the ways of learning skills.
In order to learn a skill, you need to go see a Skill Master and purchase a Skill Card from them.
Who are the Skill Master? I will explain all about them.
From the left is Power-Type Master Louis, Sense-Type Master Cochma, Charm-Type Master Tiphreth and I'm the Magic-Type Master Sephira.
You will need to buy a Skill Card that first your Job and Level from the appropriate Skill Master.
Purchase a Skill Card and then double click on the Skill Card in order to learn the skill.
But you need to have a high enough TM level as well as have enough TM points available in order to learn the skill.
You will earn 1 TM Point every time your TM level is increased.
TM Level and TM Points can be checked in the skill window. Click on the Skill Window button or press a shortcut key "S" in order to open the skill window.
The skills you've learned are registered in the Skill Window. You can use skills by double clicking on the Skill Icons before attacking Monsters.
Skills can be used more efficiently if you register them on a Quick Slot.
<<changeNPCState Magician_Sephira Magician_Sephira-1>>SKIP
<<changeNPCAnimation Magician_Sephira 0>>SKIP
<<startQuest 7>><<giveItem card-pack 1>>SKIP
Well, click on the "C" button to open up the Card Inventory. You will see one Skill Card in your inventory.

title: Rosemary-0
body:
<<changeNPCAnimation Rosemary 1>> SKIP
SKIP
Hello I am RoseMary, I'm the current leader of a group called 7-Princess Club. You look really prepared today. Let's see what you've got~
I will explain how to equip a weapon. First, you need to click on the EQUIP icon or press the shortcut key "E" to open the equipment window in order to equip the weapon. Then, open the Item Window and double click on a Item you want to use or drag the item to the Equipment Window. The same principle is applied to installing a Drill, equipping a Pet or wearing fashion items.
Let me tell you about combat. If you move the mouse near a monster you want to attack, the mouse becomes the shape of a sword. That's when you attack the Monster by clicking it.
There are two ways to find out the level of the Monster you're attacking. You can click on the right mouse button over the Monster's head, or you can press "alt" key to display the name and level of all monsters nearby the area you're in. You can make good use of the Shortcut Keys if you memorize them. Got it? <<changeNPCState Rosemary Rosemary-1>>
I need to test you to see if you have followed my tutorial carefully. Let me give you a quest. If you succeed, I promise to reward you. Do you know what happens if you don't succeed? Well, you will be punished by the members of the 7-Princess Club!
Hohoho~ Don't worry too much. You just need to hunt a Torobbit and bring me a Mini Carrot. I will reward you with a Pet as a present only if you succeed.
Wow~ I like you already! Ok then, off to get some Mini Carrots~
<<changeNPCAnimation Rosemary 0>> SKIP
<<startQuest 9>>SKIP
<<spawnMonster torobbie>>SKIP
SKIP

Looks like you're ready for the Game. Why don't you go to Blooming Cora and fill out an Application for participating in the game?<<updateQuest Rosemary>>
